President Obama has nominated Judge Joseph A. Greenaway, Jr. for the United States Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit and Judge Beverly B. Martin for the United States Court of Appeals for the Eleventh Circuit. Judge Greenaway currently sits on the United States District Court for the District of New Jersey, while Judge Martin serves on the United States District Court for the Northern District of Georgia. President Obama praised both judges for their integrity and experience, and expressed his gratitude for their service to their respective states. Judge Greenaway has been a U.S. District Court Judge in New Jersey for over 12 years and has also worked as a federal prosecutor and in private practice. Judge Martin, on the other hand, has served as an Assistant U.S. Attorney and U.S. Attorney before becoming a U.S. District Court Judge in Georgia. Both judges have received awards for their judicial excellence.